thread.title_full: Australian market set to open lower

author: news.com.au
title: lower
text:
Friday capped off its best week in almost four years.
AAP Share Share on Facebook Share on Twitter Share on Google+ Share on Reddit Email a friend THE Australian market is set for a slow start after its best week in almost four years.
The December share price index futures contract was down 18 points at 5,249.
Overseas stock markets finished last week strongly after hints US interest rates will not rise until next year, AMP Capital chief economist Shane Oliver said.
He said futures were pointing to a dip of about 10 points at Mondayâ€™s local open but not for long thanks to rising commodity prices.
Locally on Monday, Transurban Group will hold its annual general meeting and the Austraian Bureau of Statistics will release lending finance figures for August.
 Friday capped off its best week in almost four years as strength in the financial and resources sectors drove a fifth straight day of gains.
